  {
    "id": "millais-ophelia",
    "title": "Ophelia",
    "artist": "John Everett Millais",
    "year": 1852,
    "medium": "Oil on canvas",
    "dimensions": "76.2 cm × 111.8 cm",
    "location": "Tate Britain, London",
    "description": "Millais's most celebrated painting depicts Shakespeare's Ophelia floating in a stream, singing as she drowns amid wildflowers. Painted with extraordinary botanical precision from studies made on the banks of the Hogsmill River, the work epitomizes Pre-Raphaelite devotion to truth in nature.",
