    "artist": "John William Waterhouse",
    "year": 1896,
    "medium": "Oil on canvas",
    "dimensions": "98.2 cm × 163.3 cm",
    "location": "Manchester Art Gallery",
    "description": "The Greek hero Hylas is lured into a pool by water nymphs during the voyage of the Argonauts. Waterhouse renders the nymphs as pale, alluring figures half-submerged among water lilies, their dark eyes fixed on the unsuspecting youth in a scene of beautiful menace.",
