    "artist": "Dante Gabriel Rossetti",
    "year": 1874,
    "medium": "Oil on canvas",
    "dimensions": "125.1 cm × 61 cm",
    "location": "Tate Britain, London",
    "description": "Proserpine holds the fateful pomegranate that binds her to the underworld, her melancholy gaze conveying the anguish of her imprisonment. Modeled by Jane Morris, with whom Rossetti was deeply infatuated, the painting is charged with personal longing and mythological resonance.",
