    "year": 1880,
    "medium": "Oil on canvas",
    "dimensions": "269.2 cm × 116.8 cm",
    "location": "Tate Britain, London",
    "description": "A procession of identical young women descends a spiral staircase carrying musical instruments. The painting's deliberately ambiguous subject, monochromatic silvery palette, and dreamlike repetition create a hypnotic effect that prefigures Symbolism and early abstraction.",
