    "artist": "Edward Burne-Jones",
    "year": 1874,
    "medium": "Oil on canvas",
    "dimensions": "186 cm × 111 cm",
    "location": "Lady Lever Art Gallery, Port Sunlight",
    "description": "Nimue reads from a book of spells to enchant the wizard Merlin, who lies powerless in a hawthorn thicket. The sinuous trees, the serpentine figure of Nimue, and Merlin's expression of helpless resignation create a powerful image of seduction and the defeat of masculine intellect by feminine wile.",
    "image": "/paintings/burne-jones-beguiling-merlin.jpg",
    "imageCredit": "Wikimedia Commons, Public Domain",
    "movementId": "pre-raphaelite",
