    "location": "Lady Lever Art Gallery, Port Sunlight",
    "description": "Hunt painted this extraordinary work on the shores of the Dead Sea, depicting the biblical scapegoat — laden with the sins of the people — dying in the salt marshes at sunset. The desolate landscape and the animal's suffering create a powerful meditation on sacrifice and atonement.",
