    "description": "Isabella mourns over a pot of basil in which she has buried the head of her murdered lover Lorenzo — a tale from Boccaccio retold by Keats. Hunt's Isabella is draped in elaborately embroidered robes, her grief expressed through the clasp of her arms around the ornate majolica pot.",
